  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba9\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb3\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Detention of Indian fishermen",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Local Police Magistrate Court has ordered that the 5 Tamil Nadu fishermen who were arrested on charges of fishing across the border be remanded till the 19th.",
        "The five fishermen from Pudukottai district's Jagadapattinam area, who left for fishing from Kodiakkarai area in a boat, were arrested by the navy yesterday, Monday, while they were engaged in catching fish across the border at Karainagar beach, Jaffna.",
        "The arrested fishermen were produced in the District Magistrate's Court today, Tuesday, through the Department of Marine and Hydrological Resources, and the judge ordered them to be remanded until the 19th.",
        "On the other hand, the 12 Tamil Nadu fishermen who were arrested for the crime of fishing across the border last Sunday have been ordered to be remanded till the next 08th.",
        "It is noteworthy that 17 Tamil Nadu fishermen have been arrested under the crime of crossing the border in two days."
      ],
